
=Discussion=


= John Restakis and Michel Bauwens agreed on these six principles for the convergence of the open (peer production) and cooperative economy:


1. Economic democracy

2. Co-operative accumulation

3. Commons-oriented peer production and commons accumulation through open design communities

4. Sustainable development within environmental limits

5. Open, pluralist economy (including controls on enterprise size and market control)

6. Partner State, Commonification of Public Services, and Public-Civil Partnerships 


